d 'RDSTAGGER': module to estimate Staggered Regression Discontinuity with Network Interference
d
d      rdstagger estimates ATT(g,t) - the average treatment effect
d for the cohort of units first    treated in period g, measured at
d calendar time t - within a unified framework that    combines
d three identification strategies:	  (1) Regression
d discontinuity (RD): treatment eligibility is determined by a
d running	     variable crossing a known cutoff. Kernel
d weights concentrate the comparison on 	   observations
d near the cutoff.	  (2) Staggered difference-in-differences:
d units adopt treatment at heterogeneous times		 
d (cohorts), following the framework of Callaway and Sant'Anna
d (2021). This avoids		 the forbidden-comparison problem
d of two-way fixed effects estimators under	       treatment
d effect heterogeneity.        (3) Network interference: units may
d receive spillover effects through a network of	   
d neighbors. The command estimates both the direct ATT (on treated
d units) and the	    share of neighbors treated as a
d spillover proxy (Manski, 2013).    For each cohort-period cell,
d rdstagger computes a kernel-weighted DiD using the   
d pre-treatment period immediately before treatment adoption as the
d base period (g-1). 
d
d KW: ATT
d KW: treatment effect
d KW: regression discontinuity
d KW: staggered treatment
d KW: spillovers
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260516
d
d Author:    Subir Hait,  Michigan State University
d Support: email   haitsubi@@msu.edu
d
f rdstagger.ado
f rdstagger.sthlp
f rdstagger_agg.ado
f rdstagger_plot.ado
f rdstagger_pretest.ado
f rdstagger_sim.ado
f rdstagger_spillover.ado
f rdstagger_agg.sthlp
f rdstagger_plot.sthlp
f rdstagger_pretest.sthlp
f rdstagger_sim.sthlp
f rdstagger_spillover.sthlp
f rdstagger_example.do
f rdstagger_montecarlo.do
